---
title: Orange and Cashew Chicken Stir-Fry with Bell Pepper and Jasmine Rice
description: If orange chicken is your go-to whenever you grab takeout, we think you’ll be pleasantly delighted by our take. We’ll be sending you an actual orange, so you can juice it and get that freshly squeezed taste—it’s leagues more vibrant and fresh than that mystery sauce you probably know. To keep things interesting, we’re also adding bell pepper slivers and a glazed-cashew garnish. The only struggle will be to not eat this dish up before you even get it on the plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/orange-and-cashew-chicken-stir-fry-fcc117e7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/orange-and-cashew-chicken-stir-fry-5a296ba851d3f15fe04e9e02-c51a3135.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/orange-and-cashew-chicken-stir-fry-5a296ba851d3f15fe04e9e02
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 81 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 580 mg
---

Bring 1¼ cups water and a pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a small #pot. Once boiling, add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}. Cover, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Meanwhile, cut @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} into 1-inch pieces, then toss with @cornstarch{1%tsp} in a medium #bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @ginger{1%unit}, then mince until you have 1 1/2 TBSP. Core and seed @bell pepper{1%unit}, then slice into thin strips. Trim @scallions{2%unit}. Thinly slice white and light green sections; cut greens into 1-inch pieces. Zest @orange{1%unit} until you have 1 tsp zest, then halve. Squeeze ¼ cup juice from orange into a small #bowl.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a medium #pan over medium heat. Add @cashews{1%ounce} and toss until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @sugar{1%tsp} and a pinch or two of @korean chili flakes{pinch}(to taste). Cook, stirring, until cashews are coated in a sticky, lightly browned glaze, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Remove from #pan and let cool on a #plate or piece of #parchment.

Whisk together orange juice, orange zest, @sugar{1%tsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, 1 TBSP minced ginger, 1 TBSP water, and remaining @cornstarch{1%tsp} in a small #bowl. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Toss in scallions and remaining minced ginger. Cook, tossing, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove veggies from #pan and set aside. Heat another large drizzle of oil in same #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, tossing, until browned and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in sauce and bring to a simmer. Lower heat slightly and stir until sauce is thick, sticky, and coats chicken, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide rice between plates, then top with veggies and chicken. Drizzle with any remaining sauce in #pan. Garnish with cashews and sprinkle with remaining @korean chili flakes{pinch}(to taste).